**Traced (Capture47, draw EID 8080, RenderDoc PS-debug):** the frame quad outputs
`o0 = texture(gray ~0.63, ALPHA ~0.30) Ã— vertexColor(0.42,0.80,0.78 = cyan, a=1)` â†’ cyan @ ~0.3 
alpha,
alpha-blended â†’ the translucent cyan square. The **cyan is correct** (SWG space-HUD vertex-color 
theme);
the **alpha (~0.3 from the texture) is the bug** â€” the panel background shows where gl05 has it
invisible. Same shader frames the reticle gauges â†’ **one shader/element type, one root** (matches
Kenny's "probably one shader being a few wrong"). Draws involved: EID ~8028/8054/8080 (CUI quads via
`CuiLayerRenderer` â†’ `Graphics::drawQuadList` â†’ `Direct3d11_StateCache::drawQuadList`).

