   - `CuiLayer::TextureCanvas` turns empty shader into `shader/uicanvas_filtered.sht` and texture into `texture/ui_space_gauge_square.dds` at [CuiLayer_TextureCanvas.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientUserInterface/src/shared/core/CuiLayer_TextureCanvas.cpp:28) and [CuiLayer_TextureCanvas.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientUserInterface/src/shared/core/CuiLayer_TextureCanvas.cpp:108).

3. Authored pass state for `shader/uicanvas_filtered.sht` from `data_other_00.tre`:
   - Two PASS `0007` variants, both identical for the requested state:
   - `alphaBlendEnable = true`
   - `alphaBlendOperation = Add`
   - `alphaBlendSource = SourceAlpha`
   - `alphaBlendDestination = InverseSourceAlpha`
   - `alphaTestEnable = false`
   - `alphaTestReferenceValueTag = 0`
   - `alphaTestFunction = Greater`
   These fields are read in `ShaderImplementationPass::load_0007()` at [ShaderImplementation.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/ShaderImplementation.cpp:1533). Defaults match the same blend/test defaults at [ShaderImplementation.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/ShaderImplementation.cpp:920).

4. The additive radar glow/ring overlay is different:
   - `SourceResource='ui_shader_add:ui_space_radar_gauge'` at [ui_hud_space.inc](<D:/Code/SWGSource Client v3.0/ui/ui_hud_space.inc:2013>).
   - That resolves to `shader/ui_shader_add.sht` + `texture/ui_space_radar_gauge.dds`; `ui_shader_add.sht` points to `effect/ui_add.eft`.
   - Authored `effect/ui_add.eft` PASS `0009` state:
     `alphaBlendEnable=true`, `BlendOp=Add`, `Src=SourceColor`, `Dst=One`, `alphaTestEnable=false`, `alphaTestReferenceValueTag=0`.
   - PASS `0009` fields are read at [ShaderImplementation.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/ShaderImplementation.cpp:1692).

5. “One shader, one root” is true for the cyan frame and the gauge/ellipse ring elements that use `ui_space_gauge_square`: they share `shader/uicanvas_filtered.sht` and `texture/ui_space_gauge_square.dds`, then batch through `CuiLayerRenderer` by shader at [CuiLayerRenderer.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientUserInterface/src/shared/core/CuiLayerRenderer.cpp:170). It is not true for the explicit glow overlay, which uses `ui_shader_add`.

6. I found no UI shader in the scanned set `shader/ui*.sht`, `shader/uicanvas*.sht`, `shader/2d_*.sht`, or `effect/ui*.eft` with `m_alphaTestEnable = true`. So there is no authored UI alpha-test ref I found that would discard alpha `0.229`.
